<subSubSection id="77D2C3E676F1664D77062887432F3FBE" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" type="notes">
<paragraph id="17E2D20A39E0FF4DEBE97CEC2DF67BB6" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4DB2D03218DB7BE0EC5C4E0A05EEC0D5" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
The characters of our new strain of 
<taxonomicName id="EC138CEDF483BCEDDFBC21DA713F0C36" authorityName="S. Hughes" authorityYear="1953" baseAuthorityName="Sacc." class="Dothideomycetes" family="Lophiotremataceae" genus="Hermatomyces" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hermatomyces sphaericus" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="sphaericus">
<emphasis id="294EA99E9FC176688BE24BCE82CC5163" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Hermatomyces sphaericus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(KUMCC 20-0231, MFLUCC 21-0036) are similar to the type collection (K(M)-IMI 37763) in having gray black to black sporodochia, mononematous, pale brown, smooth, monoblastic, integrated, terminal, cylindrical, hyaline to pale brown conidiogenous cells and globose to subglobose conidia (
<bibRefCitation id="84EEDCB1B313809A2248C62A508C0168" author="Hughes, SJ" journalOrPublisher="Mycological Papers" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="1 - 104" refId="B11" refString="Hughes, SJ, 1953. Fungi from the Gold Coast. II. Mycological Papers 50: 1 - 104" title="Fungi from the Gold Coast. II." volume="50" year="1953">Hughes 1953</bibRefCitation>
). A multigene phylogeny indicates that novel strains clustered within the 
<taxonomicName id="C5E66B755F1D19D45A1DF3D5D453BA09" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Hermatomycetaceae" genus="H." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="H. sphaericus" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="sphaericus">
<emphasis id="739E946FC35068CB3D8032B30BEC11D1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">H. sphaericus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8DFEF17DE56B3C2A9C9517360C69C01A" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Phylogenetic RAxML tree based on analysis of a combined LSU, ITS, tub 2, tef 1 - α and rpb 2 and dataset. Bootstrap support values for ML and MP equal to or higher than 75 % and Bayesian PP equal to or greater than 0.95 are shown at nodes. Hyphens (--) represent support values less than 75 % / 0.95 BYPP. The ex-type strains are in bold and the new isolate in this study is in blue bold. The tree is rooted with Anteaglonium globosum (ANM 925.2) and A. parvulum (MFLUCC 14 - 0821). The scale bar represents the expected number of nucleotide substitutions per site." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.82.67973.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/575839" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">1</figureCitation>
). We name our strain (KUMCC 20-0231, MFLUCC 21-0036) as 
<taxonomicName id="D8921EFAFFDBEB703658089A9DB47644" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Hermatomycetaceae" genus="H." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="H. sphaericus" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="sphaericus">
<emphasis id="2B197BDBE07A9419260D4D16DBC2F0CB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">H. sphaericus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which has been reported from different plant families and genera (
<bibRefCitation id="BFC4FDF45DDE0F53E9E192176E250CD4" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5598/imafungus.2018.09.01.08" author="Koukol, O" journalOrPublisher="International Mycological Association" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="107 - 141" refId="B20" refString="Koukol, O, Delgado, G, Hofmann, TA, Piepenbring, M, 2018. Panama, a hot spot for Hermatomyces (Hermatomycetaceae, Pleosporales) with five new species, and a critical synopsis of the genus. International Mycological Association 9: 107 - 141, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5598/imafungus.2018.09.01.08" title="Panama, a hot spot for Hermatomyces (Hermatomycetaceae, Pleosporales) with five new species, and a critical synopsis of the genus." url="https://doi.org/10.5598/imafungus.2018.09.01.08" volume="9" year="2018">Koukol et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
). However, we consider this might be a species complex that need further detailed studies. Our study provides the new host records of 
<taxonomicName id="980822407B6F2230CCC149460D67F757" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Hermatomycetaceae" genus="H." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="H. sphaericus" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="sphaericus">
<emphasis id="919258D40B189C204543DD9616F7AE4A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">H. sphaericus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on 
<taxonomicName id="CBBC56333A527407804565BA4AB6870D" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Dipterocarpaceae" genus="Dipterocarpus" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dipterocarpus" order="Malvales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3A3889AE4376D06B2E110F0CE28A5AD8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Dipterocarpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. (
<taxonomicName id="0FCE410631FE1E59A84F69E454B466D6" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Dipterocarpaceae" genus="Dipterocarpus" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Malvales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Dipterocarpaceae</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="E0584A1252ACC1A7ADD7231C7A777DE9" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Ehretia" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ehretia acuminata" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acuminata">
<emphasis id="64A33F90D3A685E84C6314B3E87CE59D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ehretia acuminata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="BBBBFAF1B0ACD2F5F3651F9158504E9B" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Ehretia" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Boraginaceae</taxonomicName>
), and updates sequence data for the new collections of 
<taxonomicName id="6015D7EF8F0A291514ACB07645CC0F37" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Hermatomycetaceae" genus="H." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="H. sphaericus" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="sphaericus">
<emphasis id="EBCDF7BA2A1DFAF149E697E3931FA3CC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">H. sphaericus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
